The arrangement of the words is in favour of the genitive, as pairing, aster Horace's way, the substantives and epithets. 14. Panaeti, the Stoic philosopher and the friend of Scipio Africanus Minor. His great work was a treatise περὶ τοῦ καθήκοντος, which was the basis of Cicero's de Officiis.
